<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-044-520  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 044 520.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Jan 15 1990 v12 n3 p94(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Earlier reports of OS/2's death were greatly exaggerated. Maybe.andO;(Qandamp;A: Quindlen and Alsop) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Quindlen, Ruthann.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Predictions that OS/2 will fail in the marketplace have beenpartially refuted.andP;  A market survey by Computer Intelligence Increveals that OS/2 is achieving greater market penetration thanUnix and will surpass DOS as the operating system of choice in1991.andP;  Thirty-nine percent of users overall and 41 percent ofFortune 1000 users expect to install OS/2 by the end of 1991, butthe survey neglected the Windows operating environment.andP;  TheDepartment of Transportation (DOT) has awarded a large contract toMicrosoft because DOT is committed to installing Windows on up to40,000 microcomputers.andP;  Developers creating OS/2 applications hopethat OS/2 will surpass DOS, and some current OS/2 users proclaimthe importance of upcoming versions of the new operating system.andO;OS/2 is likely to be especially useful in complextransaction-processing environments.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Operating SystemsMarket ShareOS-2TrendsForecasting.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>